               1 Tim. 1.29 1 Cor. 5.5. And wrote to the Corinthians to Excommunicate the Incestuous person, that the spirit may be saved in the day of the Lord Jesus. The severe discipline of the Ancients, and how usual it was with them in case of Lapse, or the commission of any gross and Scandalous Crime, to impose Penances of seven or fifteen years, yea for a whole life, is well known. And of later years, St. Dunstan, Archbishop of Canterbury, enjoyn'd Edgar King of England a seven-years Penance in order to his Reformation. And therefore the Learned Dr. Hammond compares the Minor Excommunication to Spiritual Physick to be applied to the sin-sick Soul for the Recovery of its former state o
